This paper deals with improving the performance of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method for evaluating and replacing specific filters, which falls under the category of machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses gradient norms to evaluate the impact of filters, which is a common technique in optimization algorithms, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also deals with improving the efficiency of CNNs, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
